.TH "__platform_register_drivers" 9 "__platform_register_drivers" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__platform_register_drivers \- register an array of platform drivers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __platform_register_drivers
.BI "(struct platform_driver * const *drivers "  ","
.BI "unsigned int count "  ","
.BI "struct module *owner "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drivers" 12
an array of drivers to register
.IP "count" 12
the number of drivers to register
.IP "owner" 12
module owning the drivers
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Registers platform drivers specified by an array. On failure to register a
driver, all previously registered drivers will be unregistered. Callers of
this API should use \fBplatform_unregister_drivers\fP to unregister drivers in
the reverse order.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
